review_blob: Small white head. Cloudy. Bitter and grassy taste. A slight creamy mouth feel. Medium bodied. Average carbonation. A bitter and sour finish. Im not digging the after taste on this one.
Best if served very cold. Fizzy. Only plus is a creaminess. Becomes boring after a few sips. May give you the beer shits.
Dark maple syrup color. No head at all. Aroma is faint with only maple syrup that stands out the most. Medium taste with a plain watery finish. Doesnt have enough body. Weak.
Very little presence. Small to no head, slight hint of blackberry. Aroma is moderate but faint. Very little to no carbonation. Yellow color. After taste is like plain water. Weak.
